279
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:56,560
not to live with him.

280
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:00,960
So, he lives in the company dorm.

281
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,320
He brings laundry to my place

282
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,920
every weekend

283
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,400
and I make a nice meal

284
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,680
for him.

285
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,600
Now that we're in the same city,

286
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,960
we can see each other all the time.

287
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,400
It's easier for both of us.

288
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,880
Don't you want to get married?

289
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:16,720
We do.

290
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:17,880
After he graduates.

291
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,240
What about you?

292
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,440
Got a boyfriend?

293
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,320
Me?

294
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,760
Well, I had a boyfriend.

295
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,600
Handsome gentlemen and beautiful ladies,

296
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,520
join me in horse-riding tomorrow.

297
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,920
What? Horse-riding?

298
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,640
Don't just drink.

299
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,880
You need to exercise.

300
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:38,880
I can't go.

301
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,280
I've got a meeting tomorrow.

302
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,040
I can't, either.

303
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,440
I'm going to play golf tomorrow.

304
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,440
Bummer.

305
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,640
How about you three?

306
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:47,680
Count me out.

307
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:48,840
Physical exercises scare me.

308
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,200
Just let me sleep in.

309
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,200
You?

310
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,560
I am free.

311
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:53,880
But...

312
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,440
But what? You're going.

313
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,160
You?

314
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,600
I can go.

315
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,200
I am not as lazy as my sister.

316
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,520
Okay!

317
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,480
That's a deal.

318
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:02,240
Okay.

319
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:07,560
Bao Xue.

320
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,960
Where did you graduate?

321
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,280
The Central Academy of Drama.

322
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,480
Great school.

323
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,360
I heard that there are three systems in acting.

324
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:16,080
Stanislavski's system,

325
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:16,760
Brecht's system,

326
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:18,520
and the system created by Mei Lanfang.

327
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,200
I don't know about the first two.

328
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:21,000
But I think

329
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,720
Mei Lanfang's system must be the greatest one.

330
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:25,040
Which system do you use?

331
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,520
I use the system of Mei Lanfang's brother,

332
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:27,440
Mei Lanzhu.

333
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,880
Mei Lanzhu?

334
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,840
Does Mei Lanfang even have a brother?

335
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,080
I've never heard of him.

336
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,200
Don't listen to her.

337
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,160
It's not so much Mei Lanzhu

338
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,760
as she's making a joke.

339
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:38,720
I'm not making a joke.

340
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:41,000
I'm just making fun of myself, Shanshan.

341
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,240
I've graduated for three years

342
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,160
and still am an extra

343
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:45,800
on different sets.

344
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,960
I think you're so funny.

345
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,360
You should try comedy.

346
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:51,120
You don't understand.

347
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:53,760
The core of every comedy is a tragedy.

348
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,240
Just look at those legendary comedians.

349
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:57,240
Deep down inside, they are

350
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:59,480
very sensitive, fragile, and depressed.

351
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,520
People like me

352
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:01,600
that are optimistic

353
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,520
and can get over anything

354
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,120
are perfect for tragedies.

355
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,240
Because however tragic the story is,

356
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,160
I can make sure to break character afterward.

357
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:11,640
You know yourself quite well.

358
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:12,480
So, people like you

359
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:14,160
who don't take things seriously

360
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:15,440
are fundamentally

361
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:17,080
very confident, right?

362
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:22,000
Way to talk me up, Shanshan!

363
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,080
Feels great.

364
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:25,680
Shanshan.

365
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:26,800
All jokes aside,

366
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,880
if I can't even get a part as an extra,

367
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:29,840
I'll work for you.

368
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,560
Ma'am.

369
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:44,440
Do you own this jockey club?

370
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:45,920
How could I?

371
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,360
I'm just a member here.

372
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:49,560
Shanshan.

373
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,240
Seriously, I'll work for you from now on.

374
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,320
You don't even know what I do for a living,

375
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,840
and you're already applying to work for me?

376
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,000
Aren't you afraid I'll kidnap you?

377
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,480
Kidnap me?

378
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,920
I'm a nobody.

379
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:00,920
Even a kidnaper

380
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:01,920
would let me go.

381
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,400
He'd keep my clothes maybe.

382
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:05,040
Don't worry.

383
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:06,400
I won't kidnap you.

384
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,160
But maybe I'll eat you alive!

385
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,760
You've got a big appetite, Shanshan.

386
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,120
Trying to eat me alive?

387
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:12,880
Shanshan.

388
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:14,680
Bin.

389
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:16,120
I rarely see you here.

390
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:18,440
It's been long since you came here.

391
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,680
I've called you many times

392
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:20,600
asking you out for dinner

393
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,600
and you rejected me.

394
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,200
Turns out you're hiding here trying to avoid me.

395
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,040
I wasn't avoiding you.

396
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:26,520
Let's have lunch together

397
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:27,200
and we can talk.

398
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:27,880
Okay.

399
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:35,600
See?

400
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,120
That girl looks so cool

401
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,640
on the horse.

402
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,120
Will we look like her later?

403
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:41,760
No way.

404
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:46,320
Don't you have any faith in me?

405
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:49,080
Now, I'll take you to have a look at the horses here.

406
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,680
Find me a steady one.

407
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:53,440
I don't wanna fall down.

408
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,200
Don't worry.

409
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,480
I've arranged a coach for you.

410
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:56,720
You won't fall.

411
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,720
Tell you what.

412
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,320
Horses understand humans well.

413
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:01,080
But, they're also bullies.

414
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,680
The minute you stand in front of them

415
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:03,720
and they can sense

416
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,440
if you know how to ride.

417
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,920
Really, Shanshan?

418
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:10,320
How do equestrians walk?

419
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,320
I'll learn their walks

420
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,760
and see if I can trick the horse.

421
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:15,920
This is mine.

422
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:18,120
Its dad was the champion in the Dressage World Cup.

423
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:20,320
Its mom was the champion in the European Pageant.

424
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,440
A royal!

425
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:24,480
What is it called?

426
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,560
Cigar.

427
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:27,800
Miss me?

428
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:31,080
Cigar.

429
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:33,040
Shanshan.

430
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:33,920
Does it bite?

431
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:35,360
I wanna touch it.

432
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,440
Try it.

433
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:38,600
Cigar.

434
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:45,160
One, two, three.

435
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,600
Fair ladies,

436
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:48,640
can you do me a favor?

437
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:51,000
We're shooting an ad here.

438
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,520
Can you help me

439
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,520
do a scene as extras?

440
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:55,720
It's your lucky day.

441
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,320
She is

442
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,720
a professional extra.

443
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:01,800
Bao Xue?

444
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,720
Liu Liangzhou!

445
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:04,400
What a coincidence!

446
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,600
What brings you here?

447
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:07,600
You know each other?

448
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,040
Let me introduce him.

449
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:11,040
He's the photographer of my last play.

450
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:12,200
Liu Liangzhou.

451
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,800
You know how to choose a set.

452
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,000
What are you shooting?

453
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:16,920
An ad.

454
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:18,080
War Horse

455
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,080
functional beverage.

456
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,120
Jade is here, too.

457
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:25,880
She is?

458
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:27,760
Great.

459
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:28,640
Great.

460
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,200
They'll help you

461
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:30,720
with makeup.

462
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:32,080
Okay.

463
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,400
I can't go with you.

464
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,760
I've got a thing later.

465
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:35,920
I can't shoot the ad with you.

466
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,080
Practice before shooting.

467
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:37,880
Careful.

468
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:38,920
Okay.

469
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,480
Feng Xi, let's go.

470
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:41,480
Lead the way!

471
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,320
Jade!

472
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:44,960
I've got two extras for you.

473
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:45,760
Look who it is.

474
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:50,760
What are the odds!

475
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:51,760
How come you are here!

476
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,040
Where did you find her?

477
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,360
Jade, I miss you so much!

478
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:58,080
How's study?

479
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,000
Good.

480
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,880
You can't prioritize horse-riding

481
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,440
over study.

482
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,200
Bin.

483
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,800
How's business going?

484
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:08,880
Not good.

485
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,200
Tianyi.

486
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,560
Let me have a word with Ms. Shanshan.

487
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:13,120
Okay.

488
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:18,680
Shanshan.

489
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:19,920
I'm so sorry.

490
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:23,360
I'm having people keep an eye on the money.

491
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,640
Once it's in,

492
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:26,520
I'll pay you up immediately.

493
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,560
Bin, I'm not here to rush you.

494
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,160
Give me some time.

495
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:34,120
Tomorrow,

496
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:36,040
I'll pay some of the interest.

497
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,040
Bin,

498
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,880
we're friends.

499
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:42,000
I got into this business because of you.

500
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,120
You don't need to pay interest.

501
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:44,720
Just give the principal back

502
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:45,840
when the cash flow is normal.

503
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:49,920
Shanshan.

504
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:50,960
Thanks.

505
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,079
Granny.

506
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:19,359
Sis.

507
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:20,480
You're back!

508
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:22,400
Granny, where is Xiaoyu?

509
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,200
She's out.

510
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,720
She said she wanted to check on this company.

511
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,440
I'm exhausted.

512
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:46,160
Great.

513
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,720
Were you doing heavy-lifting?

514
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:52,600
I went to a spontaneous horse-riding
 with two friends.

515
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:53,520
I can't feel

516
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,160
my back and my hips anymore.

517
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,920
Granny, can you give me a massage?

518
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,720
I used to cycle to the mountains

519
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:03,800
and get spring water in my 50s.

520
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:06,040
I can't compete with you.

521
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:06,840
You were

522
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:09,240
nurtured by the love of my grandpa.

523
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:11,720
Who's stopping you to find love?

524
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:14,680
Finding love is way tiring than horse-riding.

525
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,080
If I get dumped, I'll need over a month to recover.

526
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,120
No, thanks.

527
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,440
You were asking for it.

528
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,560
I met a bad guy.

529
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:22,000
Okay?

530
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,960
Granny,

531
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:27,000
can you make me noodles?

532
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:27,720
After I'm full,

533
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,640
I'll set up a trap

534
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,400
and catch a boyfriend for you.

535
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,440
For me?

536
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,520
Don't bother.

537
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:36,320
You're the best!

538
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,040
Don't lean on the fridge.

539
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:49,600
Look at yourself.

540
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:51,920
Granny,

541
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,320
I heard you singing along the piano

542
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:55,920
when I was coming in.

543
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,240
Your voice

544
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:58,400
was so pure.

545
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,480
You don't sound like someone in their 70s at all.

546
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:03,680
I was a voice major in a normal school, after all.

547
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,560
I didn't have all the soup

548
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:06,920
in my school for nothing.

549
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:10,960
The old saying was referring to rice.

550
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,200
How come it's soup with you?

551
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:15,000
Back then, we didn't have sufficient food.

552
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,240
I left

553
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,720
all the food coupons to your grandpa.

554
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:20,760
Soup was free.

555
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:23,840
I get it.

556
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,400
You were trying to use food coupons

557
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,600
in exchange for

558
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,480
the love and obedience of my grandpa.

559
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,520
You're quite a visionary!

560
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,160
Don't try to sweet-talk me.

561
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,880
If he had really listened to me,

562
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:39,120
I wouldn't have lived such a hard life.

563
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,280
Your life is hard?

564
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,520
I think you are just too greedy.

565
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:46,000
When my grandpa was with you,

566
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:48,080
he didn't dare to

567
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:50,440
disagree with a single word

568
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,840
you said.

569
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:53,480
What more do you want?

570
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:56,640
He didn't disagree with me verbally.

571
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:59,080
But he kept giving away stuff.

572
00:19:59,080 --> 00:20:00,160
If it were not for me,

573
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,280
he'd already

574
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:02,720
given away all the family fortune.

575
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:09,360
Your mom went to Shenzhen for a job after graduation.

576
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:12,600
She moved back to Beijing when she was having you.

577
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,120
I was there to take care of her.

578
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,760
She wanted to go back to Shenzhen

579
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,320
after her maternity leave.

580
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,040
I was worried about you two,

581
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:22,520
so I asked her to leave you here

