If we pay for the house,

872
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:01,080
then it will be our home, right?

873
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,880
Two families living under the same roof.

874
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:05,800
Who'll be in charge?

875
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:07,880
Me, or Zhu Min?

876
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:10,000
We're family.

877
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:12,280
Whoever makes the right decision
 should be in charge.

878
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:17,160
Those are the most useless words in the world.

879
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:18,560
How do you define "right?"

880
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:20,720
Everyone has their reasons.

881
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:23,520
How will you decide

882
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:24,840
who's right?

883
00:31:25,320 --> 00:31:27,200
You old thing,

884
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:28,640
you're so bossy-boots.

885
00:31:29,080 --> 00:31:31,080
You were so harsh

886
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:32,800
on him just now.

887
00:31:33,080 --> 00:31:35,640
He must be heartbroken hearing all that.

888
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:37,320
That's none of my business.

889
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:39,800
I've raised him from a kid.

890
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:41,200
My conscience is clear.

891
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:48,760
Then, we bought this house.

892
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:51,240
And your uncle stopped bothering us for a while.

893
00:31:52,480 --> 00:31:54,280
6 months later,

894
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:57,960
when we had just finished decorating

895
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:01,000
and wanted to sit back and relax,

896
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,280
trouble found us again.

897
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,520
My uncle came back?

898
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:04,480
No.

899
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,800
He was afraid to see me.

900
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:09,640
He called your grandpa in secret.

901
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:12,000
Houjiang called today.

902
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:13,520
I know.

903
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,400
I need to discuss something with you.

904
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:18,920
A good thing or a bad thing?

905
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:20,160
A good thing.

906
00:32:20,160 --> 00:32:22,640
Xiaoyu is going to study in Europe.

907
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:25,120
A good thing, indeed.

908
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,720
She has two options.

909
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,040
She can either go to this uni in the UK

910
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:30,640
that only offers a partial scholarship.

911
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:33,840
But, the cost of living will be lower.

912
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:36,720
Or she can go to this uni in Norway

913
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:38,160
with full scholarship

914
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:40,760
and high cost of living.

915
00:32:42,280 --> 00:32:44,920
This is the first one to study abroad in our family.

916
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:47,040
What do you want to do?

917
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:49,520
Hear me out.

918
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:51,280
She'll be gone for a year.

919
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:53,400
It'll cost less than 200k

920
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:55,480
for tuition and living expenses.

921
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:57,520
I don't think it's too much.

922
00:32:57,520 --> 00:32:58,320
Not much.

923
00:32:58,920 --> 00:32:59,880
Not little, either.

924
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:02,000
He can send her there if he can afford it.

925
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:05,600
They just bought a house, though.

926
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:07,800
We also just bought a house.

927
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:09,360
We can't afford to fund them.

928
00:33:10,080 --> 00:33:11,040
But we still have

929
00:33:11,040 --> 00:33:13,000
1 million yuan in the checking account.

930
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:13,800
Stop.

931
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,800
Dai Wangxi, listen to me.

932
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:20,840
I only pay for the tuition fee of our children.

933
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:23,280
I paid for Houjiang's undergraduate study

934
00:33:23,280 --> 00:33:24,240
and Chengcheng's

935
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:25,400
postgraduate study.

936
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:26,400
That's it.

937
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:29,600
I've done my part.

938
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:31,480
Stop trying to

939
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:34,280
shoulder others' responsibility.

940
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:39,160
Forget about

941
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:40,400
the money in the checking account.

942
00:33:43,080 --> 00:33:45,000
I remember the day of my grandpa's cremation.

943
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,960
I went to school that afternoon.

944
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:49,320
I saw my mom crying when I got back.

945
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:52,040
I kept asking her what happened,
 but she wouldn't tell me anything.

946
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,680
It was my dad that told me what happened.

947
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,200
He said that

948
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,720
my uncle got into an argument with you.

949
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:00,480
The day your grandpa died,

950
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:03,720
your uncle called me out

951
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:05,800
at the family funeral hall.

952
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:11,679
Mom.

953
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:14,600
Your lips are so dry that they're chapped.

954
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:16,159
Have some water.

955
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:27,400
Mom.

956
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:30,080
What's your plan for the future?

957
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,560
I'll just try to get by every day.

958
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:35,040
I've got no plan.

959
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:38,440
You've been taking care of my dad for so many years.

960
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:41,440
Now that he's gone,

961
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:44,800
and you're getting older,

962
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:46,520
how about

963
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:48,080
you come with me to Hangzhou?

964
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:51,120
I'm fine here.

965
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:53,760
I'll add to your plate if I live with you.

966
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:55,080
Don't say that.

967
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:56,440
It's our duty

968
00:34:56,440 --> 00:34:58,280
to take care of you when you're old.

969
00:35:01,680 --> 00:35:05,200
You guys are already under pressure,

970
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:07,160
supporting Xiaoyu's study abroad.

971
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:07,960
Mom.

972
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:09,040
My brother's under pressure.

973
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:10,320
I'm not.

974
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:11,520
How about you

975
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:13,320
live with me in Shenzhen for a while?

976
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:15,640
You can come back whenever you want to.

977
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:16,280
Chengcheng.

978
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:17,520
I think

979
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:18,960
mom should live with me.

980
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:19,920
I won't go anywhere.

981
00:35:22,040 --> 00:35:23,480
Come back and visit me

982
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:25,720
if you miss me.

983
00:35:25,720 --> 00:35:28,000
Why are you so stubborn?

984
00:35:29,280 --> 00:35:29,960
You're

985
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:32,280
welcome to either of our houses.

986
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:33,560
Think about it.

987
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:34,760
You're already old.

988
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:36,440
It'll be too much work for you

989
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:38,560
to take care of a house this big.

990
00:35:46,720 --> 00:35:47,800
Just say it.

991
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:50,120
What do you want?

992
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:57,840
Mom.

993
00:35:59,160 --> 00:36:00,160
Here's the thing.

994
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:02,560
I do need a small favor.

995
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:04,600
But to be clear,

996
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:07,120
I won't take advantage of you.

997
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:09,480
I am

998
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:11,080
running a business.

999
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:12,280
I need money.

1000
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:14,160
I

1001
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:16,040
was planning to take out 
a loan on my house in Hangzhou.

1002
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:17,200
But that wasn't enough.

1003
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:19,040
Do you think

1004
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:21,160
you can

1005
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:23,160
lend me some money?

1006
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:25,800
Maybe we can take out a loan on this house

1007
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:28,840
and I will

1008
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:31,040
pay you back with interest.

1009
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:34,280
I knew it.

1010
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:36,680
You're up to something.

1011
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:39,800
Your father just died,

1012
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:42,080
and you're already after the house.

1013
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:44,240
Where do you want me to go?

1014
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:45,320
Come on.

1015
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,800
It's just a mortgage.

1016
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:47,680
We're not selling it.

1017
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:48,840
You'll still own it.

1018
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:50,360
What if your business fails?

1019
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,800
I'll sell the house in Hangzhou

1020
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:54,360
and pay you back.

1021
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:55,800
You just said

1022
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:57,520
the house in Hangzhou

1023
00:36:57,520 --> 00:36:58,760
is not worth this much.

1024
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:01,840
Well...

1025
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:03,360
The price will go up in years.

1026
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,320
You are

1027
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,200
always thinking about

1028
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:10,680
your self-interest.

1029
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:12,760
When your dad was alive,

1030
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,400
his savings before retirement

1031
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:17,360
and his property after retirement,

1032
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:20,520
you wanted them all.

1033
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:22,320
But did you give me any of those?

1034
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:24,080
I was wise not to give them to you.

1035
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:25,440
Do I owe you?

1036
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:27,880
I'll say this upfront.

1037
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,800
As long as I am alive,

1038
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,880
I will be in charge of this house.

1039
00:37:31,880 --> 00:37:32,640
Mom.

1040
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:34,520
You only ask us to do things for you,

1041
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:36,280
but you never do things for us.

1042
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:38,160
Other parents

1043
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:39,560
try their best

1044
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:40,680
to help their kids.

1045
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:41,680
And you?

1046
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:44,240
Well, I've said enough.

1047
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:45,280
Don't worry.

1048
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,240
I will

1049
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:47,960
pay you back in the future.

1050
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:50,040
Do I need to be

1051
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:52,480
sucked dry

1052
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:55,320
to prove that I am a good mother?

1053
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:56,240
Mom.

1054
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:58,040
Take a break, okay?

1055
00:37:58,600 --> 00:38:00,160
Have I done you any wrong?

1056
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:02,640
Have I ever starved you?

1057
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:04,600
Have I ever kept you from good education?

1058
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:05,240
There are things

1059
00:38:05,240 --> 00:38:07,680
other than food and education.

1060
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:08,920
You ask us for money to do business,

1061
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:10,960
support your kid,

1062
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:12,760
and buy a house.

1063
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:14,000
What more do you want?

1064
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:14,680
Mom.

1065
00:38:14,680 --> 00:38:16,400
Even crows feed their parents.

1066
00:38:17,680 --> 00:38:19,720
You're a father now.

1067
00:38:19,720 --> 00:38:20,720
How will you be a role model

1068
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:22,520
to Xiaoyu if you keep acting like this?

1069
00:38:22,520 --> 00:38:23,800
I want to look after you in your final years.

1070
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:26,080
Doesn't that count as repaying you?

1071
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:27,520
You want to sell my house

1072
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:30,440
and get the money to look after me

1073
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:32,560
and support your whole family.

1074
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:35,120
You and your wife are strong and capable.

1075
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:36,320
You're healthy human beings.

1076
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:38,960
And yet you're asking me, a 70-year-old, for money?

1077
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:40,320
Don't you feel guilty?

1078
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:41,640
I told you.

1079
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:43,600
I'm just putting your house on mortgage.

1080
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:47,120
If you don't believe me,

1081
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:47,720
how about this?

1082
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,120
We can

1083
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:55,320
write it down

1084
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:56,400
and sign an agreement, okay?

1085
00:38:56,720 --> 00:38:57,760
I'm not signing anything.

1086
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:00,200
What if you show it to others

1087
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:02,120
and accuse me of being insensitive?

1088
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:03,400
I'll be the bad guy in others' eyes.

1089
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:05,920
How come you just can't understand me?

1090
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:08,280
No mother is like you.

1091
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:10,360
Guarding against your own child as if I'm a thief.

1092
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:11,640
If other mothers are good enough,

1093
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:12,840
you can be their son.

1094
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:16,360
You should think before you speak.

1095
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:18,480
If you're ever ill,

1096
00:39:18,480 --> 00:39:20,280
you'll have to rely on us, won't you?

1097
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:21,560
Rely on you?

1098
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:23,640
I dare not dream of it.

1099
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:27,240
Among all the 200 bones in my body,

1100
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:29,040
there's still a backbone.

1101
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:31,520
Dai Houjiang.

1102
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:35,080
You're my son, after all.

1103
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,160
I gave birth to you, and I raised you.

1104
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,960
But now,

1105
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:44,680
you're treating me as an enemy.

1106
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:46,200
Great.

1107
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:48,200
Great!

1108
00:39:50,640 --> 00:39:51,800
From now on,

1109
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:54,520
let's cut all connections.

1110
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:56,480
I am not your mother.

1111
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:58,800
And you are not my son.

1112
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,320
If you insist,

1113
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:02,760
I won't try to talk you out of it.

1114
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:06,600
In the future,

1115
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,520
if anything happens, don't come to me.

1116
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:11,600
Go to Chengcheng instead.

1117
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:16,080
Get out of here.

1118
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:19,000
Get out!

1119
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:20,160
Mom.

1120
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:20,880
You...

1121
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:21,560
Okay.

1122
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:23,160
I'll leave.

1123
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:27,520
Stay out of this.

1124
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:28,880
It doesn't concern you.

1125
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:49,840
Don't be angry,

1126
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:51,040
granny.

1127
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:53,160
I've not spoken to your uncle

1128
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:55,200
for ten whole years already.

1129
00:40:57,080 --> 00:40:57,960
Tell me.

1130
00:40:59,040 --> 00:40:59,880
We, as parents,

1131
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:02,920
have put so much effort into raising a kid.

1132
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,320
And this is what we get.

1133
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:06,520
Did I do anything wrong?

1134
00:41:06,520 --> 00:41:08,480
Of course, not.

1135
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:10,440
But I've gotta say something.

1136
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:12,160
Do bear with me.

1137
00:41:12,440 --> 00:41:13,960
If my uncle

1138
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:16,040
comes to you for a favor,

1139
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:17,360
will you help him?

1140
00:41:17,360 --> 00:41:18,160
No.

1141
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:23,520
If he comes to apologize to me,

1142
00:41:24,280 --> 00:41:25,720
I'll forgive him.

1143
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:27,280
But again,

1144
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:29,840
if he's hungry, I'll prepare all the food he needs.

1145
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:31,680
But if he wants money, I won't give him any.

1146
00:41:31,680 --> 00:41:33,520
I've done my job as a mother.

1147
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:35,600
See?

1148
00:41:35,600 --> 00:41:37,320
You two are the same.

1149
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:39,320
No one is willing to back down.

1150
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:40,520
You're waiting for him to apologize.

1151
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:42,120
He's waiting for you to call him.

1152
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:43,360
Call him?

1153
00:41:43,360 --> 00:41:45,040
It should be the other way around.

1154
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:48,000
Did I give birth to him, or he me?

1155
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:49,400
Granny.

1156
00:41:49,400 --> 00:41:52,840
You can't play the seniority card.

1157
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:54,560
If I didn't play that card,

1158
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:58,320
can you even sit here in this house,
 worried about nothing?

1159
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:01,560
I get it.

1160
00:42:01,560 --> 00:42:03,880
You kept asking when I wouldn't tell you.

1161
00:42:03,880 --> 00:42:04,720
Now that I told you,

1162
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:06,440
how come you're on their side?

1163
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:07,960
Who's on their side?

1164
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:08,920
You are!

1165
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:09,680
I am not.

1166
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:12,840
I will always be on your side.

1167
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:16,200
It's just that after I heard the story,

1168
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:17,080
I think

1169
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:19,240
it doesn't have to be like this.

1170
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:20,960
You're saying I made a mountain out of a molehill?

1171
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:23,360
No.

1172
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:26,160
I feel for you.

1173
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:27,320
I condemn the intolerable behavior

1174
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:28,880
of my uncle!

1175
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:30,520
Over these years,

1176
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:32,680
I've never mentioned it to anyone.

1177
00:42:35,200 --> 00:42:36,560
You're right.

1178
00:42:36,960 --> 00:42:38,040
When I know too much,

1179
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:40,200
it will become a burden.

1180
00:42:42,360 --> 00:42:43,160
Granny.

1181
00:42:44,120 --> 00:42:45,280
Do you think Xiaoyu

1182
00:42:45,280 --> 00:42:46,440
knows about this?

1183
00:42:46,840 --> 00:42:49,400
She must know that I had a fallout with her dad.

1184
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:52,240
But she may not know what caused it.

1185
00:42:53,680 --> 00:42:54,800
If your uncle

1186
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:57,480
wants to tell his side of the story,

1187
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,480
I'd be

1188
00:42:59,480 --> 00:43:01,400
the unreasonable one for sure.

1189
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:04,760
So, my uncle is not so bad.

1190
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:05,720
Not so bad, my ass.

1191
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:07,560
He's just too embarrassed to tell her.

1192
00:43:09,440 --> 00:43:10,920
Granny, you're

1193
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:12,040
such a logical person.

1194
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:14,000
It's not about being logical.

1195
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:17,480
Harbor no ill-will toward others,

1196
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:20,240
but always be mindful of the ill-will
 toward yourself.

1197
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:23,400
I've never harmed anyone in my life.

1198
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:25,200
But I won't allow anyone to harm me

1199
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:27,920
that easily.
